lass=\"token punctuation\">:</span>\n\t\t<span class=\"token keyword\">pass</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">class</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">concrete</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>Base<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span>\n\n\t<span class=\"token keyword\">def</span> <span class=\"token function\">foo</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>self<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span>\n\t\t<span class=\"token keyword\">pass</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\"># this concrete class definition will produce errors at the time of instantion because</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\"># it hasnt implemented the bar method which is declared as an abstract method</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\"># in the Base class.Also the Base class cannot be instantiated since it is an Abstract class</span></code></pre></div>","timeToRead":1,"frontmatter":{"title":"Abstract Methods in Python","date":"October 20, 2020","spoiler":"Handling Abstract Methods in Python.","cta":null},"fields":{"slug":"/abstract-methods/","langKey":"en"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/abstract-methods/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/drf-jwt/","langKey":"en","directoryName":"drf-jwt","maybeAbsoluteLinks":[]},"frontmatter":{"title":"DRF and JWT"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/the-with-statement/","langKey":"en","directoryName":"the-with-statement","maybeAbsoluteLinks":[]},"frontmatter":{"title":"The With Statement in Python"}},"translations":[],"translatedLinks":[]}},"staticQueryHashes":["336482444"]}